    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-10-25T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-10-25T01:00:00-05:00" n="395"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <head>395. Memorandum of telephone conversation between <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1"
                        >Ball</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BM_1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>,
                    October 25<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d395fn1">Response to <persName
                            corresp="#p_KNS_1">Khrushchev</persName> message. No classification
                        marking. 1 p. <gloss target="#t_DOS_1">DOS</gloss>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> Papers: Lot 74 D 272,
                        Telcons—Cuba.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-10-25T01:00:00">October 25, 1962, 1
                            a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d395-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d395-1"/>
                <p>Bundy said that the President wants to go along with <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1"
                        >Ball</persName>’s version. He said that since we can’t get any agreement on
                    the longer version, they will go along with the short version. Bunday said that
                    they will have to get across to Adlai—</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> said he was talking with <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJH_1">Cleveland</persName> and that he doesn’t think we can
                    soften it any. <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> said that we are
                    going to have to think about getting <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1"
                        >McCloy</persName> down—Bundy agreed that <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1"
                        >Ball</persName> should ask <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName>
                    to come down.</p>
                <p>Bundy said that the President just came into the room and he said that he thought
                    the first clause of paragraph 3 . . . in order to give time might mean we
                    willing to give. Can’t we leave that out?</p>
                <p>Bundy and <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> agreed that the 3rd and
                    4th paragraphs could be put together.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
